text: Paepalanthus celsus is a species of plant in the Eriocaulaceae family. It is endemic to Ecuador. Its natural habitats are subtropical or tropical moist montane forests and subtropical or tropical high-altitude shrubland. ==References== Category:Eriocaulaceae Category:Endemic flora of Ecuador Category:Least concern plants Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot
